Object_Heading	Object_Text	aRequirementObjectType	Section_number	ID.Status	aResponsibility	a_EB_PO_Status	a_ZF_PO_Status
1 Task Management			1	1_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	Requirements for the Task Sheet view, task editing, WBS hierarchy, task dialogs, and task-level features.	information	1.1	PO-TASK-INFO-001.0	Not relevant		
1.1 Task Sheet View			1.1	1_1_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	The system shall provide a Task Sheet view as a full-width hierarchical table that is the default view on application startup.	functional requirement	1.1.1	PO-TASK-001.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Task Sheet shall display the following columns: ID, Status Icon, Name, Duration, Start, Finish, % Done (with progress bar), Predecessors, and Resource Names.	functional requirement	1.1.2	PO-TASK-002.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Predecessors column shall display enriched text in the format '<Task ID> – <Task Name>' for each predecessor.	functional requirement	1.1.3	PO-TASK-003.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Task Sheet shall support inline cell editing for Name, Duration, and % Done.	functional requirement	1.1.4	PO-TASK-004.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	Double-clicking a task row in the Task Sheet shall open the Task Information dialog.	functional requirement	1.1.5	PO-TASK-005.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Task Sheet shall support collapsing and expanding summary (parent) task rows.	functional requirement	1.1.6	PO-TASK-006.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Task Sheet shall display rows with 36 px row height and alternating background colours.	functional requirement	1.1.7	PO-TASK-007.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
1.2 Row Status Icons			1.2	1_2_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	Each task row shall display one status icon drawn as a pixmap with hover tooltip: purple diamond for milestones, blue page for tasks with notes, amber triangle for % complete > 100, orange circle for overdue tasks, red circle for critical path tasks (< 100% complete).	functional requirement	1.2.1	PO-TASK-008.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The blue 'has notes' icon shall take precedence over overdue / critical icons in the same row.	functional requirement	1.2.2	PO-TASK-009.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
1.3 WBS Hierarchy			1.3	1_3_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	The system shall support a Work Breakdown Structure (WBS) hierarchy with summary tasks and child tasks at multiple levels of indentation.	functional requirement	1.3.1	PO-TASK-010.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	Summary tasks shall display rolled-up duration, start, and finish dates from their subtasks.	functional requirement	1.3.2	PO-TASK-011.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The system shall support adding tasks as subtasks (children) of a selected summary task.	functional requirement	1.3.3	PO-TASK-012.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
1.4 Task Information Dialog			1.4	1_4_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	The system shall provide a Task Information dialog with six tabs: General (name, duration, start, finish, % complete, milestone flag), Predecessors (predecessor task links), Resources (resource assignments with units), Custom Fields (project-defined task fields), Notes (free-text notes field), and Jira (read-only Jira linkage data from the sidecar file).	functional requirement	1.4.1	PO-TASK-013.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Task Information dialog shall include a checkbox indicating whether the task is currently pinned to the Timeline View, allowing the user to add or remove it.	functional requirement	1.4.2	PO-TASK-014.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Jira tab of the Task Information dialog shall display the linked Jira key and current Jira status as read-only fields, a clickable URL to browse the ticket in the Jira web UI, and an explanatory message when the task has no Jira linkage.	functional requirement	1.4.3	PO-TASK-014a.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Resources tab of the Task Information dialog shall populate its resource selector only from resources present in the current project; each assignment row shall display the resource name resolved by unique ID, never showing placeholder text such as '(unknown)'.	functional requirement	1.4.4	PO-TASK-020.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	Each assignment row in the Resources tab of the Task Information dialog shall include a per-row '✕' delete button; clicking it shall remove that specific assignment from the table and cancel any pending assignment for that row without affecting other rows.	functional requirement	1.4.5	PO-TASK-021.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
1.5 Critical Path			1.5	1_5_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	The system shall compute and highlight the critical path. Tasks with zero total float shall be marked as critical when the zero-float-critical option is enabled.	functional requirement	1.5.1	PO-TASK-015.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	Completed tasks (% complete = 100) shall be excluded from critical path computation.	functional requirement	1.5.2	PO-TASK-016.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
1.6 Add and Delete Tasks			1.6	1_6_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	The system shall allow adding a new task via the Insert key or the Add Task ribbon button.	functional requirement	1.6.1	PO-TASK-017.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The system shall allow deleting a selected task via the Delete key or the Delete Task ribbon button.	functional requirement	1.6.2	PO-TASK-018.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	Adding and deleting tasks shall be undoable via the undo/redo history.	functional requirement	1.6.3	PO-TASK-019.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
</OBJECTS>
